  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.12344" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>Colombo Ceylon<lb/> October 30 1883</dateline>
        <opener>Dear Sir,</opener>

        <p> I must apologize for delay on replying to your letter of May 16 on account of many engagements &amp;amp; frequent absence from <placeName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.251">Colombo</placeName>. </p>

        <p> I shall be happy to assist you if possible but I do not know how to obtain the books you refer to. I send you <pb
            facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/> by post a small packet of publications &amp;amp; shall be gratified if they are of service to you. </p>
        <p>Unfortunately the language in printed books is higher than that spoken which latter contains a considerable number of expressions not to be found in the books. </p>

        <p>By far the best qualified person to answer any enquiries on the subject is J. H. Eaton Esq.. Advocate oft he Supreme Court<note
            n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <persName
              ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1427">John Henry Eaton</persName> (1829-1906). Vgl. die Briefe <ref
              target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/context:hsa.letters.1427?locale=de">HSA 02653-02655</ref>, die er an <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.109">Schuchardt</persName> gerichtet hat.</note>, <placeName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.249">Kandy</placeName>
          <note n="2" place="foot" type="editorial">Stadt in <placeName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.5857">Ceylon (Sri Lanka)</placeName>.</note>
        </p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Yours truly</salute>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2711">J. Scott</persName>
          </signed>
        </closer>
      </div>
    </body>
